118
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,770
I think you sent it to me before.

119
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:01,680
Right?

120
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,500
It's not finished yet.

121
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:07,160
Faces in amber light,

122
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:09,240
yet somehow time stands still,

123
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:10,360
on the ground,

124
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:12,960
windows drawn everywhere.

125
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,620
Let time peel away endlessly,

126
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:16,860
years passing, days flowing,

127
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,600
keeping connections, preserving light,

128
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:19,860
like a lifetime apart,

129
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:21,780
just like the morning sun.

130
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:24,370
Morning sun.

131
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:27,420
I've never seen a sunrise before.

132
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:33,360
I think your writing is really good.

133
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:34,000
Actually,

134
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,930
you have a real talent for writing,

135
00:09:36,520 --> 00:09:38,050
why don't you keep writing?

136
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:41,800
I believe

137
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:43,360
